      "actor": "gsd-codebase-mapper",
      "content": "You are subagent gsd-codebase-mapper, role: pragmatic audit of each Hivemind tool/surface — determine REAL status.\n\nFor EACH of the following surfaces, answer these 4 questions with EVIDENCE:\n\n**Questions:**\n1. DOES IT WORK? (any test passing? any import path valid? any logic beyond stubs?)\n2. WHO USES IT? (grep for imports/usage — is it consumed by anything?)\n3. WHAT FUNCTION DOES IT SERVE? (what problem does it solve for the harness?)\n4. VERDICT: KEEP (working + needed), FIX (broken but needed), REMOVE (dead code/not needed)\n\n**Surfaces to check:**\n\n### A. Tools (src/tools/)\n\n1. **delegate-task** (src/tools/delegation/delegate-task.ts)\n   - grep for imports of this tool in plugin.ts or anywhere\n   - check if tool is registered in plugin.ts\n   \n2. **delegation-status** (src/tools/delegation/delegation-status.ts)\n   - same checks\n\n3. **session-tracker** tool (src/tools/hivemind/session-tracker.ts)\n   - same checks\n\n4. **session-context** tool (src/tools/hivemind/session-context.ts)\n   - same checks\n\n5. **session-hierarchy** tool (src/tools/hivemind/session-hierarchy.ts)\n   - same checks\n\n6. **hivemind-pressure** tool (src/tools/hivemind/pressure.ts or similar)\n   - same checks\n\n7. **hivemind-doc** tool (src/tools/hivemind/doc.ts or similar)\n   - same checks\n\n8. **config-primitive** tool (src/tools/config/ or similar)\n   - same checks\n\n9. **prompt-analyze/prompt-skim** tools (src/tools/hivemind/ or src/tools/prompt/)\n   - same checks\n\n10. **bootstrap-init/bootstrap-recover** (src/tools/hivemind/ or src/features/bootstrap/)\n    - same checks\n\n11. **run-background-command** (src/features/background-command/)\n    - same checks\n\n12. **hivemind-trajectory** (src/tools/hivemind/)\n    - same checks\n\n13. **hivemind-sdk-supervisor** (src/tools/hivemind/)\n    - same checks\n\n14. **hivemind-agent-work-create/export** (src/tools/hivemind/)\n    - same checks\n\n15. **validate-restart** (src/tools/hivemind/)\n    - same checks\n\n### B. Coordination modules (src/coordination/)\n\n16. **DelegationManager** (src/coordination/delegation/manager.ts)\n17. **ConcurrencyQueue** (src/coordination/concurrency/queue.ts)\n18. **CompletionDetector** (src/coordination/completion/detector.ts)\n19. **CommandDelegationHandler** (src/coordination/command-delegation/)\n20. **Spawner** (src/coordination/spawner/)\n\n### C. Task-management modules (src/task-management/)\n\n21. **Continuity** (src/task-management/continuity/)\n22. **Journal** (src/task-management/journal/)\n23. **EventTracker** (src/task-management/event-tracker/)\n24. **Recovery** (src/task-management/recovery/)\n25. **Trajectory** (src/task-management/trajectory/)\n26. **Lifecycle** (src/task-management/lifecycle/)\n\n### D. Features (src/features/)\n\n27. **Session-tracker** (src/features/session-tracker/) — we know it's write-only, but is it USED by LLM tools?\n28. **Background-command/PTY** (src/features/background-command/)\n29. **Bootstrap** (src/features/bootstrap/)\n30. **Doc intelligence** (src/features/doc-intelligence/)\n31. **Prompt packets** (src/features/prompt-packets/)\n32. **Pressure** (src/features/pressure/)\n33. **SDK supervisor** (src/features/sdk-supervisor/)\n34. **Work contracts** (src/features/work-contracts/)\n\n### E. Hooks (src/hooks/)\n\n35. **Lifecycle hooks** (src/hooks/lifecycle/)\n36. **Guard hooks** (src/hooks/guards/)\n37. **Observer hooks** (src/hooks/observers/)\n38. **Transform hooks** (src/hooks/transforms/)\n39. **Composition** (src/hooks/composition/)\n\n### F. Routing (src/routing/)\n\n40. **Session entry** (src/routing/session-entry/)\n41. **Behavioral profile** (src/routing/behavioral-profile/)\n42. **Command engine** (src/routing/command-engine/)\n\nFor each: check with glob + grep. Be FAST. Skip detailed reading — just check:\n- File exists?\n- Registered in plugin.ts?\n- Any test file exists?\n- grep for imports from other modules?\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT: One line per surface:\n`[N].